==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Champlain period
<hw>Cham*plain" pe"ri*od</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>A
subdivision of the Quaternary age immediately following the Glacial
period; -- so named from beds near Lake Champlain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The earlier deposits of this period are diluvial in
character, as if formed in connection with floods attending the melting
of the glaciers, while the later deposits are of finer material in more
quiet waters, as the alluvium.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Champleve</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
